 instead. Artemis-commons offers utilities but resolves its own dependencies. The good news is that there's no need for extra Maven dependencies or Docker images. However, I should be cautious about optional upstream unit tests that rely on artemis-unit-test-support or log4j; they aren't necessary unless those tests require those helpers. Maybe I should just suggest no_action for now and research the artifact's compile dependencies.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"no_action\",\n  \"summary\": \"artemis-commons is a standalone utility/common API artifact; its resolved runtime needs are already transitive, and meaningful tests can exercise utilities without broker Docker, extra test dependencies, or required system properties.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The reported javac failure is API drift in org.apache.activemq.artemis.utils.Base64 in 2.38.0: constants/methods such as DONT_BREAK_LINES and decodeToObject are gone, so tests must use the current Base64 API rather than adding setup.\",\n    \"Upstream Artemis project tests may use project-local test support or logging bindings, but these are not required to exercise artemis-commons public utility behavior in the reachability metadata scaffold.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0185053cf516e2c1016a3f321f0da481959cd8af12797726bf\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 847, "output": 698, "cacheRead": 39424, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 40969, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782526481064, "responseId": "resp_0185053cf516e2c1016a3f321186a481958c0904e9e0cdd422"}, "toolResults": []}
